     7	# Hedge Fund Model
     8	## Mandate and investment universe
     9
    10	- Educational, historical AI-assisted crypto research MVP.
    11	- Long-only, unlevered daily spot USDT universe; cash is explicit.
    12	- Strategy sleeves: technical, econometric, ML and cross-sectional scoring.
    13	- Future: multi-CEX automation, but no live order submission is enabled.
    14
    15	---
    16
    17	# Hedge Fund Model
    18	## AI/ML and agent interaction
    19
    20	- Classical indicators are transparent baseline signals.
    21	- Logistic regression, gradient boosting, AutoReg/GARCH and pooled scoring are used.
    22	- Agents emit score, confidence, horizon, cutoffs and reason codes.
    23	- Aggregation proposes exposure; deterministic risk can veto or move to cash.
    24
    25	---
    26
    27	# Risk Management
    28	## Taxonomy and metrics
    29
    30	- Market, drawdown/tail, concentration/correlation and liquidity/capacity risk.
    31	- Model, data and operational failures are tracked separately from returns.
    32	- Metrics include volatility, VaR/CVaR, drawdown, exposure, turnover and costs.
    33	- Level 5 health status: `ok`.
    34
    35	---
    36
    37	# Risk Management
    38	## AI support and deterministic controls
    39
    40	- GARCH/realized volatility and regime state inform risk budgets.
    41	- Pre-allocation risk blocks stale, illiquid or invalid inputs.
    42	- Post-allocation risk validates weights, turnover, concentration and cash.
    43	- Fail-safes include volatility cash approval, invalid feature alerts and reconciliation checks.
    44
    45	---
    46
    47	# Portfolio Management
    48	## Theory and "optimal" portfolio
    49
    50	- MPT and minimum variance give transparent objectives but face estimation error.
    51	- Equal weight and inverse volatility remain robust baselines.
    52	- CVaR/downside methods address tail risk directly.
    53	- Submitted methods were selected on validation, not on final-test returns.
    54
    55	---
    56
    57	# Portfolio Management
    58	## Static, dynamic and large universe
    59
    60	- Level 3: 5-7 assets, exactly prior 12-month estimation, static OOS hold.
    61	- Level 4: calendar/drift/signal/risk rebalance policy.
    62	- Level 5: point-in-time 100+ universe, top-K 25, capacity and turnover controls.
    63	- Target weights become next-open simulated orders through one shared broker.
    64
