    66
    67	# System Architecture
    68	## End-to-end block diagram
    69
    70	```text
    71	Frozen OHLCV -> quality gate -> causal features -> signal agents
    72	  -> orchestrator -> pre-risk -> allocator -> rebalance controller
    73	  -> post-risk -> order generator -> simulated broker -> ledger
    74	  -> metrics, monitoring, notebook and deck
    75	```
    76
    77	Future CEX adapters are disabled; simulator artifacts are the submitted evidence.
    78
    79	---
    80
    81	# System Architecture
    82	## Interactions, monitoring and roadmap
    83
    84	1. Completed daily bar creates features.
    85	2. Agents emit typed proposals with cutoffs and confidence.
    86	3. Risk and portfolio layers approve, cap or reject.
    87	4. Orders fill at next open; ledger writes gross/net metrics.
    88	5. Monitoring records freshness, drift, disagreement, incidents and runtime.
    89
